<br>
1.  Maybe the server didn't have time to record the kill before the crash? how long was emp dead before the server crashed?<br>
<br>
2. Lag is hard to confirm. The GMs don't sit in the server room and watch which server is lagging.. How do they know it wasn't your ISP.<br>
<br>
3. that one shouldn't have taken a week.<br>
<br>
4. There are a lot of petitions daily.. They responded to your as fast as they could I'm sure. I don't think GMs have the ability to reset abilities.<br>
<br>
5. One followed the rules one didn't guess which.<br>
<br>
6. Sharing is one of those things in the EULA that Verant uses to protect themselves.. Have you seen anyone banned for using EQw?<br>
<br>
7. Yea thats silly but its their rule.<br>
<br>
8.  Remember a lot of people are volunteers.. Therefore they don't get paid for their work.. When people don't get paid they are likely to do their job less efficiently.<br>
<br>
When you really think about it.. A lot of the rules makes sense.  CS for any company is one of the departments that are hard to do well especially when the majority are volunteer.<br>
<br>
The worst thing about CS is they are usually only needed in a problem and most people who come in are either hostile from the beginning or short tempered.  The CS members are also human and they make mistakes that doesn't make them dumb or uncaring.<br>
<br>
remember many of the rules in place are designed to prevent cheating.. How many people know others that tried to take advantage of a bug or whatever to gain extra equipment unfairly?  Remember when that Sharlock pack or whatever it is was made LORE was it? and Verant asked people to list items that were lost when they logged in.. Well how many people said they had CoFs and cobalt BPs or whatever when they did not?<br>
<br>
Thats why reimbursement rules are against the victim. <p><center>
