</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/bquelliousquaterstherebirth.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=saltamontes>Saltamontes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=Green>Moderator</font></span><br>  Posts: 455<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(9/19/02 11:31:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=526.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another Solid Read</span><hr size=1> Gaelron....<br>
<br>
1.  I work for a webhosting company that hosts about five thousand sites.... with the backup software we use it's possible to restore files to a specific minute.  If EQ chooses not to use software powerful enough to support their systems then that is THEIR inability to provide quality service.  The point of a LOG file is to keep track of events as they happen.  If the logs are not being kept current they are useless.  It should happen right away, and a few minutes should be more than enough time.<br>
<br>
2.  I don't deny people lag and I don't deny it's impossible for them to keep track of lag.  My cynical point was this.... even when they know they are having problems they blame it on the user.  Been to Ssrae or Seru lately?  People that originally reported that lag were told they needed to update their video cards.  Nevermind the fact the zones were brought down a few days later to patch something that was obviously serverside.  Also it's retarded that it takes more than 3 hours to get a response to a rez petition when your corpse's timer only lasts that long.<br>
<br>
3.  Agreed.<br>
<br>
4.  I didn't actually expect them to reset my ability, my point was that I've /bug reported this on 5 different occasions yet none of the Guides/GM's had even heard of it before (they have a section of the GM board dedicated to common bugs for informational purposes so the CS staff isn't completely ignorant).  Obviously the people taking care of the /bug reports communicate very well with the CS department.<br>
<br>
5.  I understand there's rules to be followed out there and I know the rules for such cases.  My point is why give out conflicting messages like that?  It makes CS a roll of the die.  If you get an asshole GM you are stuck, if you get a nice GM you win.  What's to stop me from re-petitioning the same item in the hopes I get a different decision.  Oh wait that's causing more work for GM's if I do that, maybe they should just make up their minds and be consistent in the first place.<br>
<br>
6.  Of course you won't see anyone banned for using eqw, it's not exactly easy to prove.  When I /reported someone admitting they were breaking the rules I would assume that those rules were put there for a reason.  If you're not going to enforce them why bother?<br>
<br>
My comments aren't so much directed at the guides either, they're directed at GM's (who are paid for what they do).  They're the ones who leave the red petitions in queue, not the guides.  I started out working for not much more than they did but with hard work and efficiency I've been able to move up in the ranks quite well.  If EQ CS provides no manner by which GM's can advance then that is their flawed system that is the cause of the problem.  If I take weeks to address a customer's problem you're damn sure I'll hear about it from my boss.  The point of this posters thread was that they weren't really accountable to anyone so what's the point in trying to perform well?  Everyone would pass any course if they were free to grade themselves.....<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>
When dealing with fools what have unreasonable demand on CS, there is no way to win.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I totally agree with this statement.  What I don't agree with is classifying every single person who has issues with customer service as being a fool who expects too much.  If someone has a problem and I don't have it solved within 5 minutes and they're bitching at me for not helping them, I'd consider that unreasonable.  If someone has a problem and it takes me weeks to resolve that problem while I make no real effort towards fixing things and generally ignore them, then the customer has every right to be upset. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/bquelliousquaterstherebirth.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=saltamontes>Saltamontes</A> at: 9/19/02 11:32:00 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/u26hesseth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>26Hesseth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(9/20/02 1:29:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=526.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another Solid Read</span><hr size=1> LOL they have over 70 CS people.. Hmmm Me thinks they are counting the window washers and guys who take out the trash. <br>
