Voices of rallos <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/ubulvaihammersson.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BulvaiHammersson</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Dar Knight</span><br>  Posts: 163<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(9/20/02 6:53:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=526.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another Solid Read</span><hr size=1> Tsk, you two assume too much. I have petitioned, my own demands were not unreasonable. I am thus not a fool. The people I was referring to were very specifically called fools because of their unreasonable demands. <br>
<br>
I work in CS, essentially, as I am a claims rep for a major insurer. My job is exactly like what I did as a Guide for Verant 2 years ago. The only difference is that my RL jobs deals with honest to God serious problems that frikken matter, not piddly shite little BS problems like someone admitting that a friend shared their account.<br>
<br>
To each person, their personal issue is enormous. It is the CS rep's job to try and consider that persons feeling by treating their problem with respect. After the 700th frikken goon that asks you to spawn Zephyl so they can get their frikken jboots, then bitches at you for not doing it, you get a tad jaded. After the 3000th person whines to you about dying to lag, you get actively cynical.<br>
<br>
Lag is a BS issue. TFB Salta, there's a whole lotta internet between you and VI that could be the source of that lag. They sure as hell can't control it. I sympathize that you died and had corpse recovery problems, but suck it up and move on. If I had a frikken dollar for every time someone begged me for a GM Rez as a Guide....<br>
<br>
I'm not saying that thier CS is great, it ain't. All I'm saying is take a step back and look at what yer bloody well whining about. It's a damned game that you pay less than a buck an hour to play. Entertainment don't come any cheaper than that. It's also a game that some 400000 other people pay less than a buck an hour to play, and they all have terribly important petitions too.<br>
<br>
Recently, VI set a new record, 100000 people on. So, how many GM's were online at that time? How many Guides? How many do you expect they should have for that many simultaneous users? The math don't work, there's no way for it to work and be economic.<br>
<br>
As to the system being against you, people lie. People lie about lag death, item loss, all kinds of crap. Why? Because they aren't looking a real person in the face when they're lying. I remember sitting in LGuk one night, and watching this gnome pull a massive train. Little shit died horribly. About 10 minutes later, zone crashes. Once I manage to get back, that same gnome sends a petition demanding a rez because he died due to the zone crash. I refused his rez request and issued a warning, but that's a rare opportunity to catch a liar in the act.<br>
<br>
VI has their CS set up to try and save money, fuckin sue em for trying to be profitable. They have their CS set up to try and maximize the knowledge of their Guides by using actual players, sue em for using an abundant natural fanboy resource. <br>
<br>
The point I am making is that you might want to try, just try, to look at it objectively. As a former Guide and a guy that works the RL version of Guiding every day, VI's CS is at least tolerable enough. Like I said, you want better service, pay for it. That's what Legends is for. <p>a_Bearhat01<BR>
